HEADWORD: Iodism
<hw>I"o*dism</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Med.)</fld> <def>A
morbid state produced by the use of iodine and its compounds, and
characterized by palpitation, depression, and general emaciation, with a
pustular eruption upon the skin.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Iodize</ent>⟦br⟧
